org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.clc.cas

Interface CasFileVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAlignedReadCasVisitor, AbstractCasFileVisitor, AbstractReadCasVisitor, Cas2Consed, CasFileVisitorAdapter, CasGappedReferenceDataStoreBuilderVisitor

    public interface CasFileVisitor
    CasFileVisitor is a FileVisitor implementation for visiting CLC Bio's .cas assembly files.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • visitAssemblyProgramInfo

        void visitAssemblyProgramInfo(String name,
                              String version,
                              String parameters)
        Visit the invocation of the clc assembler that was used to create this .cas file.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the assembler used.
        version - version of the assembler used.
        parameters - assembler parameters invoked to create .cas file.

      • visitMetaData

        void visitMetaData(long numberOfReferenceSequences,
                   long numberOfReads)
        Visit meta data for this .cas file.
        Parameters:
        numberOfReferenceSequences - total number of reference sequences in this .cas file. NOTE: It is possible that not all the references had reads aligned to them.
        numberOfReads - total number of reads contained in this .cas file.

      • visitNumberOfReadFiles

        void visitNumberOfReadFiles(long numberOfReadFiles)
        Visit the number of files that contain all the read data in this .cas assembly.
        Parameters:
        numberOfReadFiles - number of files containing read data should always be >=0.

      • visitNumberOfReferenceFiles

        void visitNumberOfReferenceFiles(long numberOfReferenceFiles)
        Visit the number of files that contain all the reference data in this .cas assembly.
        Parameters:
        numberOfReferenceFiles - number of files containing read data should always be >=0.

      • visitReferenceFileInfo

        void visitReferenceFileInfo(CasFileInfo referenceFileInfo)
        Visit the CasFileInfo for all the reference files used in this .cas assembly.
        Parameters:
        referenceFileInfo - a CasFileInfo containing all data about the reference files used; never null.

      • visitReadFileInfo

        void visitReadFileInfo(CasFileInfo readFileInfo)
        Visit the CasFileInfo for a single read file or read mate pair. This method will be called n times where n is the sum of the number of fragment read input files and the number of mated pairs of read input files used in this .cas assembly.
        Parameters:
        readFileInfo - a CasFileInfo containing all data about the read files used; never null.

      • visitScoringScheme

        void visitScoringScheme(CasScoringScheme scheme)

      • visitReferenceDescription

        void visitReferenceDescription(CasReferenceDescription description)
        Visit a CasReferenceDescription of one of the references used in this assembly. This method will be called n times where n is the number of references used in this cas file.
        Parameters:
        description - the CasReferenceDescription; will never be null.

      • visitContigPair

        void visitContigPair(CasContigPair contigPair)
        Contig pairs are currently not used in CLC reference assembly so this method will not get called however it is a place holder for when it is eventually included.
        Parameters:
        contigPair - the CasContigPair; will never be null.

      • visitEnd

        void visitEnd()

      • halted

        void halted()

      • visitMatches

        CasMatchVisitor visitMatches(CasFileVisitor.CasVisitorCallback callback)
        Visit each a match. This method will be called once for every read in ALL the input sequence files; even for reads that don't align!
        Parameters:
        callback - the CasFileVisitor.CasVisitorCallback that can be used to halt parsing.
        Returns:
        a non-null CasMatchVisitor to actual visit this match; or null to skip this read.
